trans-unit.source: Specifies the new visibility timeout value, in seconds, relative to server time.

trans-unit.source: The response XML for the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation is returned in the following format.
trans-unit.target: The response XML for the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation is returned in the following format.

trans-unit.source: The <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>MessageID</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> element is a GUID value that identifies the message in the queue.
trans-unit.target: The <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>MessageID</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> element is a GUID value that identifies the message in the queue.

trans-unit.source: This value is assigned to the message by the Queue service and is opaque to the client.
trans-unit.target: This value is assigned to the message by the Queue service and is opaque to the client.

trans-unit.source: This value may be used together with the value of the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>PopReceipt</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> element to delete a message from the queue after it has been retrieved with the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation.
trans-unit.target: This value may be used together with the value of the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>PopReceipt</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> element to delete a message from the queue after it has been retrieved with the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> operation.

trans-unit.source: The value of <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>PopReceipt</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> is also opaque to the client; its only purpose is to ensure that a message may be deleted with the <link xlink:href="0c7e3383-d6a5-473b-9109-101d5cc86628" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Delete Message</link> operation.
trans-unit.target: The value of <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>PopReceipt</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> is also opaque to the client; its only purpose is to ensure that a message may be deleted with the <link xlink:href="0c7e3383-d6a5-473b-9109-101d5cc86628" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Delete Message</link> operation.

trans-unit.source: The <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>InsertionTime</unmanagedCodeEntityReference>, <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>ExpirationTime</unmanagedCodeEntityReference>, and <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>TimeNextVisible</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> elements are represented as UTC values and formatted as described in RFC 1123.
trans-unit.target: The <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>InsertionTime</unmanagedCodeEntityReference>, <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>ExpirationTime</unmanagedCodeEntityReference>, and <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>TimeNextVisible</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> elements are represented as UTC values and formatted as described in RFC 1123.

trans-unit.source: The <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>DequeueCount</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> element has a value of 1 the first time the message is dequeued.
trans-unit.target: The <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>DequeueCount</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> element has a value of 1 the first time the message is dequeued.

trans-unit.source: This value is incremented each time the message is subsequently dequeued.
trans-unit.target: This value is incremented each time the message is subsequently dequeued.

trans-unit.source: The <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>DequeueCount</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> element is returned in the response body only if the queue was created with version 2009-09-19 of the Queue service.
trans-unit.target: The <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>DequeueCount</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> element is returned in the response body only if the queue was created with version 2009-09-19 of the Queue service.

trans-unit.target: Authorization

trans-unit.source: This operation can be performed by the account owner and by anyone with a shared access signature that has permission to perform this operation.
trans-unit.target: This operation can be performed by the account owner and by anyone with a shared access signature that has permission to perform this operation.

trans-unit.source: The message content is retrieved in whatever format was used for the <link xlink:href="0a3c4fcc-0b0b-4331-87a1-01d13f3de86e" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Put Message</link> operation.
trans-unit.target: The message content is retrieved in whatever format was used for the <link xlink:href="0a3c4fcc-0b0b-4331-87a1-01d13f3de86e" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">Put Message</link> operation.

trans-unit.source: When a message is retrieved from the queue, the response includes the message and a pop receipt value, which is required to delete the message.
trans-unit.target: When a message is retrieved from the queue, the response includes the message and a pop receipt value, which is required to delete the message.

trans-unit.source: The message is not automatically deleted from the queue, but after it has been retrieved, it is not visible to other clients for the time interval specified by the <parameterReference>visibilitytimeout</parameterReference> parameter.
trans-unit.target: The message is not automatically deleted from the queue, but after it has been retrieved, it is not visible to other clients for the time interval specified by the <parameterReference>visibilitytimeout</parameterReference> parameter.

trans-unit.source: If multiple messages are retrieved, each message has an associated pop receipt.
trans-unit.target: If multiple messages are retrieved, each message has an associated pop receipt.

trans-unit.source: The maximum number of messages that may be retrieved at a time is 32.
trans-unit.target: The maximum number of messages that may be retrieved at a time is 32.

trans-unit.source: The client that retrieves the message is expected to delete the message after it has been processed, and before the time specified by the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>TimeNextVisible</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> element of the response, which is calculated based on the value of the <parameterReference>visibilitytimeout</parameterReference> parameter.
trans-unit.target: The client that retrieves the message is expected to delete the message after it has been processed, and before the time specified by the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>TimeNextVisible</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> element of the response, which is calculated based on the value of the <parameterReference>visibilitytimeout</parameterReference> parameter.

trans-unit.source: The value of <parameterReference>visibilitytimeout</parameterReference> is added to the time at which the message is retrieved to determine the value of <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>TimeNextVisible</unmanagedCodeEntityReference>.
trans-unit.target: The value of <parameterReference>visibilitytimeout</parameterReference> is added to the time at which the message is retrieved to determine the value of <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>TimeNextVisible</unmanagedCodeEntityReference>.

trans-unit.source: A message that is retrieved with a certain <parameterReference>visibilitytimeout</parameterReference> can reappear again before that specified timeout has elapsed, due to clock skew.
trans-unit.target: A message that is retrieved with a certain <parameterReference>visibilitytimeout</parameterReference> can reappear again before that specified timeout has elapsed, due to clock skew.

trans-unit.source: Note that a client could infer that a message has already been dequeued by a different client based on the pop receipt, which is unique for each dequeueing of a message.
trans-unit.target: Note that a client could infer that a message has already been dequeued by a different client based on the pop receipt, which is unique for each dequeueing of a message.

trans-unit.source: If a client’s pop receipt no longer works to delete or update a message, and the client receives a 404 (Not Found) error, then the message has been dequeued by another client.
trans-unit.target: If a client’s pop receipt no longer works to delete or update a message, and the client receives a 404 (Not Found) error, then the message has been dequeued by another client.

trans-unit.source: Typically, when a consumer retrieves a message via <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference>, that message is usually reserved for deletion until the <placeholder>visibilitytimeout</placeholder> interval expires, but this behavior is not guaranteed.
trans-unit.target: Typically, when a consumer retrieves a message via <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>Get Messages</unmanagedCodeEntityReference>, that message is usually reserved for deletion until the <placeholder>visibilitytimeout</placeholder> interval expires, but this behavior is not guaranteed.

trans-unit.source: After the <placeholder>visibilitytimeout</placeholder> interval expires, the message again becomes visible to other consumers.
trans-unit.target: After the <placeholder>visibilitytimeout</placeholder> interval expires, the message again becomes visible to other consumers.

trans-unit.source: If the message is not subsequently retrieved and deleted by another consumer, the original consumer can delete the message using the original pop receipt.
trans-unit.target: If the message is not subsequently retrieved and deleted by another consumer, the original consumer can delete the message using the original pop receipt.

trans-unit.source: When a message is retrieved for the first time, its <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>DequeueCount</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> property is set to 1.
trans-unit.target: When a message is retrieved for the first time, its <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>DequeueCount</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> property is set to 1.

trans-unit.source: If it is not deleted and is subsequently retrieved again, the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>DequeueCount</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> property is incremented.
trans-unit.target: If it is not deleted and is subsequently retrieved again, the <unmanagedCodeEntityReference>DequeueCount</unmanagedCodeEntityReference> property is incremented.

trans-unit.source: The client may use this value to determine how many times a message has been retrieved.
trans-unit.target: The client may use this value to determine how many times a message has been retrieved.
